parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear shock absorbers can cause the motorcycle to experience severe shaking, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Rear shocks tear out of the frame when going over a bump
rear swing arm pivot shaft wants to pull it further than the shock will allow
severe shaking in the front while traveling at 50 mph or more
rear shock bolts shearing off the top.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed repair of recalls can lead to continued safety risks and frustration for vehicle owners.

difficulty stopping the vehicle
increased risk of accidents.

engine noise or knocking sounds.
